Karzai to Remove Two Afghan Ministers Close to U.S., WSJ Says

-- B y   V i v e k   S h a n k a r
-- 
2011-04-07T22:24:47Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-07/karzai-to-remove-two-afghan-ministers-close-to-u-s-wsj-says.html
Afghan President  Hamid Karzai  is
planning to remove Defense Minister Abdul Rahim Wardak and
Finance Minister Omar Zakhilwal from their posts because he sees
them as too close to the U.S., the Wall Street Journal reported,
citing unidentified diplomats and Afghan officials.  Karzai’s spokesman, Waheed Omer, said the details aren’t
final, according to the Journal.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Vivek Shankar at 
 vshankar3@bloomberg.net  